Author: wicked_irony678
Text: Have you tried a first gen antipsychotic? They typically don't have they weight gain/insulin resistance profile that second generation or atypical antipsychotics have.

Author: RosieNP
Text: Don't know how long you've been on topamax, bit it helps more as time goes on. As for the antipsychotics, there are a few that don't really cause weight gain. Abilify and Geodon, for example. I take Vraylar and it didn't make me gain anything.
